# THIS IS THE REQUIRED PACKAGES LIST FOR GSB GNOME 2.23.90
#
# The following is a list of packages that can replace official Slackware packages.
#
# Packages listed under 'Required' are Slackware packages that must be replaced
# by corresponding GNOME SlackBuild versions in order to use GNOME 2.23.90 on 
# Slackware 12.1. Reasons for their replacement are given within brackets.
#
# Packages listed under 'Optional' are packages which replace official Slackware 
# packages, but their replacement are only necessary for added functionality, or 
# certain GNOME applications.  Their replacement is recommended, but not required
# if you do not plan to use certain applications, or are dead set against replacing
# any Slackware provided packages.
#
# List last updated: August 30th, 2008 (fidesratio)
#

***********************************************
Slackware 12.1 is required to run GNOME 2.23.90
***********************************************

-- Required Package Replacements for GNOME 2.23.90 on Slackware 12.1 --

glib2:            ( > 2.15 required by libgnome 2.23, gvfs 0.99.5, nautilus 2.23.90)
gtk+2:            ( > 2.13 required by libgnome 2.23, gvfs 0.99.5, gnome-panel 2.23.90)
cairo:            ( > 1.6  required by gtk+2 > 2.13)
dbus-glib:        ( > 0.76 required by gnome-panel 2.23.90, gnome-applets 2.23.89)
libwnck:          ( > 2.22 required by Metacity 2.23, and GNOME 2.23 at large)
alsa-lib:         ( >= 1.0.17a required by pulseaudio 0.9.11, libcanberra, gnome-control-panel)

-- Optional Replacements --

mozilla-firefox:  ( 3.0.1 found testing/ section.  Built against xulrunner-1.9.0.1)
compiz-fusion:    ( Slackware comes with compiz 0.7.4, compiz-fusion is cooler though and offers GNOME support)
libgsf:           ( Slackware's libgsf lacks GNOME support; required for GNOME Office applications like Gnumeric)
